messages.message:
Hi,
I forgot my password to env running in local, which is connected to the Dogfood database.  I’m not sure if the user auth for Dogfood is the same as for the local environment. I can log in to Dogfood using the same credentials, but I’m unable to access the local. Unfortunately, the reset password link doesn’t seem to be working, as I don’t get any email to reset my password.

Can someone please help?

If you are using dogfood db, the credential should be the same. Did you just switched to used dogfood db? Maybe try restart/flush redis cache.
Reset password should work locally as well :thinking_face:
